All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Administrator
Represents an administrator in the hospital management system.
AdministratorMenu
Represents the menu interface for administrators.
Appointment
Represents an appointment between a patient and a doctor.
AppointmentOutcomeRecord
Represents the outcome of a completed appointment, including details like service type, prescribed medications, and consultation notes.
AppointmentOutcomeSystem
Manages the appointment outcome records within the hospital management system.
AppointmentStatus
Enum representing the various statuses an appointment can have.
AppointmentSystem
A system to manage user appointments, including the ability to create, update, and cancel appointments.
Diagnosis
Represents a diagnosis with detailed medical information.
Dispensed
Enum representing whether a medication has been dispensed or not.
Doctor
Represents a doctor in the hospital management system.
DoctorMenu
Represents the menu interface for doctors.
HMS
Hospital Management System (HMS) that manages user login, patient registration, and user HMS.data persistence.
InputHandler
Utility class for handling user input and validation.
MedicalRecord
Represents a patient's medical record in the Hospital Management System.
MedicalRecordSystem
System to manage medical records, including saving, updating, and loading records.
Medication
Represents a medication prescribed during an appointment.
Menu
Abstract class representing a menu for a specific type of user.
MenuInterface
 
Patient
Represents a patient in the Hospital Management System.
PatientMenu
Represents the menu interface for patients.
Pharmacist
Represents a pharmacist in the hospital management system.
PharmacistMenu
Represents the menu interface for pharmacists.
ReplenishStatus
Enum representing the various statuses for a replenishment request in the hospital management system.
Stock
Represents a stock entry for a specific medicine in the hospital management system.
StockReplenishRequest
Represents a stock replenish request in the system.
StockSystem
The StockSystem class handles the management of stocks and replenish requests in the system.
User
Represents a user in the hospital management system.
UserManagementSystem
Utility class to manage user authentication and role-specific access.
UserMenuInterface
Interface representing user-specific functionality in the system.
UserRole
Enum representing the different user roles in the hospital management system.
